The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Day I Highlights
                                                                                                                       7                                      Day I Highlights
                      
	 By playing his 169th Test, Sachin Tendulkar became the most capped player in Test history. Steve Waugh with 168 Tests had held the record since 2003 when he went past Alan Borders record of 156 Tests.         
	 India have now lost 8 tosses (Dhoni 7, Sehwag 1) on the trot in Tests. India last won the toss in Kanpur (2nd Test) vs Sri Lanka in November 2009.         
	 When on 8, Kumar Sangakkara became the highest run-scorer at the P. Sara Oval. Sanga has scored 756 runs now in 8 Tests. He bettered the record of Aravinda deSilva who has scored 688 runs in 6 Tests on this ground.         
